# .easignore controls which files are uploaded to EAS Build.
# When this file exists, EAS uses it INSTEAD of .gitignore to decide what to ship.
#
# Strategy: mirror .gitignore but explicitly include google-services.json
# (which is gitignored for security but MUST reach the builder for FCM).
#
# Direct, hard-coded link — no secret resolvers, no app.config.js scripts.

# Standard ignores (kept out of EAS uploads, same as .gitignore)
node_modules/
.expo/
.expo-shared/
dist/
web-build/
*.log
.DS_Store
ios/
android/
.env*.local
.idea/
.vscode/
*.pem
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision
*.orig.*
firebase-service-account*.json

# NOTE: We intentionally do NOT list google-services.json here
# so EAS Build receives it and the FCM credentials are baked into
# the production AAB exactly like a manual Expo build.
